## Architecture: 3-Tier Justification System

Per the real UL Lexicon (lexicon.md §0.4):

| Tier | Name                        | Criterion                                     |
|------|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| T1   | Geometrically Forced        | Theorem — the only consistent construction    |
| T2   | Structurally Distinguished  | Motivated, canonical, but alternatives exist  |
| T3   | Conventional                | Design decision — one of multiple options     |

**T1 is mathematics. T2 is motivated mathematics. T3 is engineering.**

The game's element/modality/cosmic system = T3 (conventional game-layer semantic coordinates).
The 5 geometric primitives = T1 (mathematically forced).

---

## Tier 1 — Geometrically Forced (The 5 Real UL Primitives)

These are the atomic alphabet of Universal Language. Not invented. Discovered.
The Unique Grounding Theorem (formal-foundations.md §4.5) proves the mapping is unique.

```yaml
tier_1_primitives:
  - ul_symbol: point
    ul_primitive: Point
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 1  # AtomicCarrier
    semantic_primitive: Existence
    geometric_description: >
      The minimum act of meaning. Asserts that something IS.
      Dependency rank 0 — presupposed by all other primitives.
      Maximally symmetric — invariant under all rotations.
    sigma_ul_expression: "e1 (an atomic entity)"
    movement_primitive: tap
    animation_ref: point_tap
    glyph: "•"
    phonetic: pɔɪnt
    # T3 game-layer mappings (conventional)
    element: N/A
    modality: Core
    cosmic_force: Core

  - ul_symbol: line
    ul_primitive: Line
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 1  # AtomicCarrier
    semantic_primitive: Relation
    geometric_description: >
      Two points connected by a straight segment.
      The unique minimum structure introducing directionality.
      1 degree of freedom. Geometric realization of predicate(e1, r, e2).
    sigma_ul_expression: "predicate(e1, r, e2) -> a (minimal assertion)"
    movement_primitive: step_line
    animation_ref: line_walk
    glyph: "―"
    phonetic: laɪn
    element: Air
    modality: Fixed
    cosmic_force: Order

  - ul_symbol: angle
    ul_primitive: Angle
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 1  # AtomicCarrier
    semantic_primitive: Quality
    geometric_description: >
      Two rays sharing a vertex. Requires two Lines at a Point.
      Unique way to introduce Quality — the character of a relationship.
      Parameterized by theta, a continuous spectrum of quality.
    sigma_ul_expression: "modify_relation(m_theta, r) -> r'"
    movement_primitive: angle_pose
    animation_ref: angle_pose_anim
    glyph: "∠"
    phonetic: æŋɡəl
    element: Fire
    modality: Cardinal
    cosmic_force: Power

  - ul_symbol: curve
    ul_primitive: Curve
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 1  # AtomicCarrier
    semantic_primitive: Process
    geometric_description: >
      A non-straight continuous path. A relation whose direction changes
      continuously along its length. Curvature kappa(s) parameterizes rate
      of change. Requires 2D embedding. Introduces Process — becoming, change.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (curvature profile kappa(s) is geometric data)"
    movement_primitive: arm_curve
    animation_ref: curve_arm_anim
    glyph: "〰"
    phonetic: kɜːrv
    element: Water
    modality: Mutable
    cosmic_force: Flux
```

---

## Tier 1 — Enclosure Variants (Geometrically Forced by Symmetry)

The circle (maximum symmetry SO(2)) and triangle (minimum polygon) are T1.
The square is T2 (structurally distinguished but not the only 4-sided option).

```yaml
tier_1_enclosure_variants:
  - ul_symbol: circle
    ul_primitive: Enclosure
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 2  # Distinguished parameter
    enclosure_symmetry: "SO(2) — infinite rotation group, maximum symmetry"
    semantic_meaning: "Universal, Complete, Abstract — the most general kind of concept"
    geometric_description: >
      Closed curve with constant curvature, all points equidistant from center.
      Maximum symmetry of any planar closed curve. The unique maximum-symmetry enclosure.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (boundary shape is geometric; enters via abstract() modifier)"
    movement_primitive: spin
    animation_ref: spin_360
    glyph: "○"
    phonetic: sɜːrkəl
    element: Water
    modality: Mutable
    cosmic_force: Void

  - ul_symbol: triangle
    ul_primitive: Enclosure
    ul_tier: T1
    ul_level: 2  # Distinguished parameter
    enclosure_symmetry: "D3 — dihedral group of order 6"
    semantic_meaning: "Fundamental, Atomic, Irreducible — the simplest kind of concept"
    geometric_description: >
      The minimum polygon (3 sides — fewest sides that can enclose area).
      Jordan Curve Theorem. Unique minimum-complexity enclosure.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (D3 boundary shape is geometric; enters via abstract() modifier)"
    movement_primitive: step_sequence_triangle
    animation_ref: triangle_footwork
    glyph: "△"
    phonetic: traɪæŋɡəl
    element: Fire
    modality: Cardinal
    cosmic_force: Alpha
```

---

## Tier 2 — Structurally Distinguished

Square is T2 (distinguished tessellation property but not uniquely forced).
Wave and spiral are T2 curve variants (canonical but not the only periodic/expanding curve).

```yaml
tier_2_symbols:
  - ul_symbol: square
    ul_primitive: Enclosure
    ul_tier: T2
    ul_level: 2  # Distinguished parameter
    enclosure_symmetry: "D4 — dihedral group of order 8"
    semantic_meaning: "Structural, Systematic, Ordered — the organized kind of concept"
    geometric_description: >
      The unique regular polygon that tessellates the Euclidean plane by itself
      with only translations. Distinguished among 4-sided polygons.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (D4 boundary shape is geometric; enters via abstract() modifier)"
    movement_primitive: box_step
    animation_ref: box_step_anim
    glyph: "□"
    phonetic: skwɛər
    element: Earth
    modality: Fixed
    cosmic_force: Order

  - ul_symbol: wave
    ul_primitive: Curve
    ul_tier: T2
    ul_level: 2  # Distinguished parameter
    curve_property: "Periodic curvature — alternating sign. Single Fourier component."
    semantic_meaning: "Rhythm, Oscillation, Alternation — the canonical wave process"
    geometric_description: >
      A curve whose curvature alternates sign periodically.
      Simplest periodic function (single Fourier component, minimal harmonic content).
      Distinguished among all periodic curves.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (alternating curvature is geometric data)"
    movement_primitive: arm_wave
    animation_ref: wave_arm
    glyph: "~"
    phonetic: weɪv
    element: Air
    modality: Mutable
    cosmic_force: Chaos

  - ul_symbol: spiral
    ul_primitive: Curve
    ul_tier: T2
    ul_level: 2  # Distinguished parameter
    curve_property: "Monotonically increasing radius. Periodic in angle, monotonic in radius."
    semantic_meaning: "Growth, Development, Evolution, Unfolding"
    geometric_description: >
      A curve whose distance from center point monotonically increases.
      The unique curve class simultaneously periodic in angle and monotonic in radius.
      Distinguished among open expanding curves.
    sigma_ul_expression: "— (monotonic radial increase is geometric data)"
    movement_primitive: spiral_turn
    animation_ref: spiral_turn_anim
    glyph: "🌀"
    phonetic: spaɪrəl
    element: Air
    modality: Mutable
    cosmic_force: Flux
```

